        "Enforcing exact orthogonality via traditional Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) imposes a severe $\\mathcal{O}(K^3)$ computational bottleneck and injects non-differentiable discontinuities into the optimization trajectory. We conclusively bypass this limitation by executing gradient descent directly on the Stiefel manifold $\\mathbb{V}_{k,d_m} = \\{ \\mathbf{V} \\in \\mathbb{R}^{d_m \\times k} \\mid \\mathbf{V}^\\top \\mathbf{V} = \\mathbf{I}_k \\}$ [@edelman1998geometry]. \n",
